<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>So, I like everything about the new built-in treesitter except for how it overrides <code>mark-sexp</code>, <code>backward-up-list</code> and other sexp bindings, especially in C++ it completely breaks the otherwise pretty good sexp navigation. Is there a way I can retain the navigation functionality from the old <code>c++-mode</code> while keeping other treesitter functionality like highlighting, indentation etc?</p> <p>Note that when I describe key, bindings like <code>C-M-Spc</code> don&#39;t seem to be bound to other custom functions upon enabling treesitter, so I am not sure what&#39;s changing their behavior.</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/pushqrex"> /u/pushqrex </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/1330ouc/how_to_disable_treesits_override_of_mark_sexp_and/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/1330ouc/how_to_disable_treesits_override_of_mark_sexp_and/">[comments]</a></span>